properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 3:29AM PST until January 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Lingering convergence zone will allow for snow to
continue through much of the morning, especially near Stevens
Pass as snow levels continue to drop. Additional snow
accumulations of 2 to 4 inches possible across the Passes.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Darrington, Index, Skykomish, Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Northwest Avalanche Center expects high
avalanche danger to continue through through Wednesday. Check
nwac.us for the latest avalanche conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING ABOVE 3000 FEET
